<dl id="n41003a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41003a">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41003a"> 3(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> justice of the / peace</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A <mark>Justice of the Peace</mark> is a magistrate, and is entrusted with &ldquo;the conservation of the peace and the hearing and determination of charges in respect of offences against it.&rdquo; <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 9</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
